symbol{k}$ is always perpendicular\nto the flow. In unsteady flows, straining modifies the vorticity gradient and\nhence $\\boldsymbol{k}$, and may account for significant energy transfers.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 20 May 2020 21:24:01 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-12-30"}
