 100 MeV/fm$^3$. However, under these constraints, the maximum neutron\nstar mass is limited to $ \\lesssim 2.06 M_{\\odot}$. No strong signatures from\nquark matter were found on the radius and the tidal deformability for neutron\nstar masses below $1.8\\, M_\\odot$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 21 May 2020 09:55:19 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sun, 19 Jul 2020 13:55:26 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-07-21"}
