lities. Consequently, a\ncorridor having high number of dynamic segments along with poor performance\nduring normal days would be a candidate for adaptive control. A case study was\nconducted on 11 corridors within Des Moines, Iowa where Merle Hay Road and\nUniversity Avenue were identified suitable for adaptive control.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 20 May 2020 16:13:50 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-05-25"}
